 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Kyutei Omuro is a traditional Japanese mansion, built in 1937. While most people shoot this scene straight on with a reflection of the garden on the polished wood table, I prefer this angled shot that shows more of the room itself.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2306_A7R08173-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2306_A7R08173-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Rainy Day in Kyoto・京都で雨の日</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230602/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Rainy Day in Kyoto・京都で雨の日" /><published>2023-06-02T00:00:00-07:00</published><updated>2023-06-02T00:00:00-07:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/rainy-day</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230602/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
